  ('Member.MemberPhoneTTYTDD', 'en', 'Member Phone Tty/Tdd', 'TTY/TDD stands for Teletypewriter/Telecommunications Device for the Deaf. This involves a user terminal with keyboard input and printer or display output used by the hearing and speech impaired. The device contains a modem and is used over a standard analog phone line. If a recipient does not have a corresponding terminal device, TTY/TDD users dial a relay service composed of operators who receive the typed messages, call the recipients and speak the messages to them. The operators also type the responses back to the TTY/TDD user.', 'https://dd.reso.org/DD2.0/Member/MemberPhoneTTYTDD/', NULL, '2.0', 'reso_official_csv'),
